docs/working/REVIEW_FINDINGS.md:1394:The reviewed run packets and progress entries for `002EY`, `002F`, and `002FL` refer to logs under `.ralph/runs/<run-id>/evidence/terminal-logs/`, but the committed run folders contain only root-level gate result files; no `evidence/terminal-logs/` directories exist for those three runs. The final root gate logs are useful and green, but the missing red/green paths weaken auditability, especially for frontend permission and E2E infrastructure work. This repeats the evidence-path issue found in the 2026-07-03 architecture review.
