The independent reviews converge on four substantive defects: resource action authority is still bypassed and untested in the real Workbench container; the credit/approvals seam is circular and leaves workflow-event ownership in credit; witness malformed JSON can escape the envelope and its verification folio is not snapshotted; and new permission denials continue a source-contract error-code drift. I’m converting these into narrowly scoped corrective slices and tightening the downstream Workbench/tracer dependencies before recording the review.
